  p समाधिBot: What would you call this new piece of artwork?
  p India: Well… it’s a new made up thing I made. I call it the bewilder-frog.
  p समाधिBot: The bewilder-frog? I like that name!
  p India: It wears a mask because it tries to hide its face, because its face doesn’t really look
    like a normal frog, so it wears a mask all the time.
  p समाधिBot: Is its face bewildering? Or is it a total mystery??
  p India: Well… its face is kind of like grey black white colored.
  p समाधिBot: Oh… not a normal frog face at all.
  p India: Uh-uh. And usually they’re covered with scratches and bite marks, because when something
    sees it, it automatically gets so frightened and mad at the same time, even though it didn’t do
    anything. So it just bites, scratches, and does whatever it wants.
  p समाधिBot: I’ve seen animals act like that. Tell me about the cape. Why does he wear a cape?
  p India: Well, they don’t really like being on the ground for that long, because they just don’t
    really like any animals around. And so they climb up a tree, jump, and they kind of glide for a
    moment, and then they land on another tree.
  p समाधिBot: Does the cape help them glide?
  p India: Yeah, it kind of helps them glide, because they eat like once a month or once a week.
    They’re not really that much weighted. They’re light weighted.

